wiki.content: On ASTROWORLD’s 14th track, we see Travis hook up with Quavo and Takeoff of the Migos over thumping production from Cardo and 30 Roc, two producers that had a huge 2018. Beyond that, Travis and Quavo also released a collab album late last year: Huncho Jack, Jack Huncho. The album also had a Takeoff verse on “Eye 2 Eye” – the chorus of this song shares a similar flow to several parts of “Eye 2 Eye.” Quavo has appeared on both of Travis' studio albums: he was on “Oh My Dis Side” off of Rodeo, and on “Pick Up the Phone” from Birds in the Trap Sing McKnight. Quavo and Takeoff also featured on “Sloppy Toppy” off Travis' Days Before Rodeo mixtape. Scott was also on Migos' last two albums: “Kelly Price” from Culture and “White Sand” from Culture II. In the documentary “Look Mom I Can Fly” available on Netflix, we see on Travis Scott’s notebook that this track was originally titled “WHO WHAT WHEN WHY”. Takeoff was featured on Travis and Quavo’s joint 2017 album, Huncho Jack, Jack Huncho, on the track “Eye 2 Eye.” Travis also featured on Migos‘ “Kelly Price” in 2017 and “White Sand,” in 2018. “WHO? WHAT,” debuted at #43 on the Billboard Hot 100 during the week of August 18th, 2018. As of May 19th, 2019, the track has not received a higher ranking on the chart. Read more on Last.fm.
